
[1]canicule

   CANICULE, n. A star in the constellation of Canis Major, called also
   the dog-star, or Sirius; a star of the first magnitude, and the largest
   and brightest of all the fixed stars. From the rising of this
   heliacally, or at its emersion from the suns rays, the ancients
   reckoned their dog-days.
